🐾 CatCare PK – UX/UI Case Study

 📌 Overview

CatCare PK is a mobile application concept designed specifically for cat owners in Pakistan. The app focuses on health tracking, reminders, community support, and simplified pet management in one centralized platform.
Unlike global pet apps that target all animals, this solution is tailored specifically for cats, addressing localized needs and common challenges faced by Pakistani pet owners.

 🎯 Problem Statement:

Many cat owners in Pakistan face the following issues:

- Forgetting vaccination and feeding schedules
- Difficulty tracking weight and health history
- Lack of quick access to trusted veterinarians
- No centralized platform to connect with other cat owners
- Stress due to scattered information

Existing pet apps are:

- Too broad (covering all pets)
- Not localized
- Overloaded with unnecessary features

There is a need for a focused, simple, and empathetic solution.

💡 Solution:

CatCare PK provides:

- A centralized health dashboard
- Smart reminders & alerts
- Calendar scheduling system
- Community interaction feature
- Social post sharing
- Vet & services discovery

All designed with simplicity and emotional comfort in mind.

 👤 Target Audience:

- Cat owners in Pakistan
- First-time pet parents
- Busy professionals
- Students with pets
- Families with indoor cats

 🧠 UX Research Approach:

- Informal interviews with cat owners
- Competitor analysis of global pet apps
- Identifying common pain points
- Feature prioritization using MVP strategy

 🗂 Information Architecture:

Main Navigation (Bottom Bar):

- Home
- Diet
- Community
- Reminders
- Profile

Additional Screens:

- Splash Screen
- Login / Register
- What You Can Manage Page
- Create Post
- Open Community Chat

 📱 Core Features:

 1️⃣ Home Dashboard:

- Cat profile summary
- Weight tracking
- Health score indicator
- Integrated calendar
- Upcoming reminders & alerts

 2️⃣ Reminders

- Vaccination alerts
- Feeding schedule
- Grooming reminders
- Water intake tracking
- Toggle notifications

 3️⃣ Community

 Instagram-style post feed
- Like, comment, share
- Open community chat
- Ask questions & get advice

 4️⃣ Create Post

- Upload image/video
- Add caption
- Select visibility

- 5️⃣ What You Can Manage

- Health management
- Diet & nutrition
- Vet services
- Community engagement
- Profile management

- 6️⃣ Profile

- Manage cats
- Health reports
- App settings
- Notification controls
- Premium options

 🎨 Design System

- Soft pastel color palette
- Rounded UI components
- Minimal iconography
- Clear typography hierarchy
- Emotional & friendly tone

Design Principle:
“Reduce stress, increase clarity.”

 🔄 User Flow

1. Splash Screen
2. Register / Login
3. Create Cat Profile
4. Explore Home Dashboard
5. Set Reminders
6. Join Community
7. Track Health Regularly

🚀 Future Improvements

- Emergency vet locator with map integration
- AI-based health suggestions
- Vet booking system
- Growth analytics charts
- Multi-cat support enhancement

 📊 Key UX Learnings

- Focused apps create stronger value than generalized ones
- Emotional design matters in pet-related products
- Simplicity increases trust
- Clear hierarchy improves usability


 🛠 Tools Used

- Figma
- Wireframing tools
- UX research methods
- Prototyping

 📌 Status

This is a UX/UI concept project created as part of my internship learning journey.

